Caroline Wozniacki smiled and blew kisses to the crowd after winning for the first time since her break-up with Rory McIlroy.

The world No 17 said she had a ‘clear mind’ and was feeling revived after a holiday in Miami with Serena Williams.

Wozniacki, who decided to take a break after crashing out of the French Open in the first round following her split with McIlroy, said: ‘Serena and I had a good time with some of our other friends.’ 

