But British No 2 Dan Evans slammed the umpiring at Eastbourne after he lost  6-2, 6-3 to German qualifier Tobias Kamke.

‘The guy was a shambles at the start,’ said Evans. ‘I don’t understand why he wasn’t listening to what I said, he basically thought he was right.’

Britain’s Kyle Edmund was another first-round casualty, falling to American Sam Querrey 7-6, 6-3.

